{
  "info": {
    "name": "CQRS Multi-Service Demo",
    "description": "Test collection for the spring-boot-cqrs multi-service example (Spring Boot 4).\n\nRequires RabbitMQ running. Start all 3 services:\n\n./gradlew :examples:multi-service:order-service:bootRun\n./gradlew :examples:multi-service:inventory-service:bootRun\n./gradlew :examples:multi-service:notification-service:bootRun\n\nDemonstrates cross-service CQRS with commands, events, and queries over RabbitMQ.\n\nFlows:\n- Cross-service QUERY: Order Service queries stock from Inventory Service\n- Cross-service COMMAND: Order Service sends ReserveInventoryCommand to Inventory Service\n- Cross-service EVENTS: OrderPlacedEvent, InventoryReservedEvent, InventoryRejectedEvent fan out to multiple services\n- AggregateRoot: Order uses record() and pullEvents() for domain event sourcing\n- Validation middleware: PlaceOrderCommand validated with JSR-380\n- Custom middleware: LoggingMiddleware in Order Service",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "orderBaseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8090", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "inventoryBaseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8091", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "notificationBaseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8092", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Setup - Verify pre-seeded inventory",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get LAPTOP-001 stock",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Stock is 10', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body.productId).to.eql('LAPTOP-001');",
            "    pm.expect(body.productName).to.eql('Gaming Laptop');",
            "    pm.expect(body.availableStock).to.eql(10);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventoryBaseUrl}}/api/inventory/products/LAPTOP-001"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get KEYBOARD-001 stock",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Stock is 50', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body.productId).to.eql('KEYBOARD-001');",
            "    pm.expect(body.availableStock).to.eql(50);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventoryBaseUrl}}/api/inventory/products/KEYBOARD-001"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Cross-service QUERY - Check stock from Order Service",
      "description": "Order Service sends GetProductStockQuery via RabbitMQ to Inventory Service and receives the response via RPC.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Check LAPTOP-001 stock via Order Service",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Returns stock from Inventory Service via RabbitMQ', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body.productId).to.eql('LAPTOP-001');",
            "    pm.expect(body.productName).to.eql('Gaming Laptop');",
            "    pm.expect(body.availableStock).to.eql(10);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders/stock/LAPTOP-001"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Place order - SUCCESS flow (command + event cross-service)",
      "description": "POST /api/orders triggers:\n1. PlaceOrderCommand handled locally (AggregateRoot creates Order, records OrderPlacedEvent)\n2. OrderPlacedEvent published cross-service via RabbitMQ → Inventory + Notification receive it\n3. ReserveInventoryCommand sent cross-service via RabbitMQ → Inventory Service reserves stock\n4. InventoryReservedEvent published cross-service → Order confirms, Notification records it",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Place order for LAPTOP-001 (triggers cross-service command + events)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
            "pm.test('Returns order ID', () => {",
            "    const id = pm.response.text();",
            "    pm.expect(id).to.be.a('string').and.not.be.empty;",
            "    pm.collectionVariables.set('orderId1', id);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"productId\": \"LAPTOP-001\",\n  \"quantity\": 2,\n  \"customerEmail\": \"test@example.com\"\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify stock decreased (cross-service command worked)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Stock decreased to 8', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body.availableStock).to.eql(8);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventoryBaseUrl}}/api/inventory/products/LAPTOP-001"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify order is CONFIRMED (cross-service event received)",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "prerequest", "script": { "exec": [
              "// Brief wait for async event processing via RabbitMQ",
              "setTimeout(() => {}, 1500);"
            ]}},
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('Order is CONFIRMED', () => {",
              "    const body = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('CONFIRMED');",
              "    pm.expect(body.productId).to.eql('LAPTOP-001');",
              "    pm.expect(body.quantity).to.eql(2);",
              "});"
            ]}}
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId1}}"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Check notifications (cross-service events received)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get all notifications",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Contains ORDER_PLACED notification', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    const orderPlaced = body.find(n => n.type === 'ORDER_PLACED');",
            "    pm.expect(orderPlaced).to.not.be.undefined;",
            "});",
            "pm.test('Contains INVENTORY_RESERVED notification', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    const reserved = body.find(n => n.type === 'INVENTORY_RESERVED');",
            "    pm.expect(reserved).to.not.be.undefined;",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{notificationBaseUrl}}/api/notifications"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Place order - REJECTION flow (insufficient stock)",
      "description": "Same flow as success, but Inventory Service rejects due to insufficient stock.\nOrder transitions to REJECTED via cross-service InventoryRejectedEvent.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Place order for KEYBOARD-001 (quantity exceeds stock)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
            "pm.test('Returns order ID', () => {",
            "    const id = pm.response.text();",
            "    pm.expect(id).to.be.a('string').and.not.be.empty;",
            "    pm.collectionVariables.set('orderId2', id);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"productId\": \"KEYBOARD-001\",\n  \"quantity\": 100,\n  \"customerEmail\": \"reject@test.com\"\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify order is REJECTED",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "prerequest", "script": { "exec": [
              "setTimeout(() => {}, 1500);"
            ]}},
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('Order is REJECTED', () => {",
              "    const body = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('REJECTED');",
              "});"
            ]}}
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId2}}"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify KEYBOARD-001 stock unchanged",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Stock unchanged at 50', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body.availableStock).to.eql(50);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventoryBaseUrl}}/api/inventory/products/KEYBOARD-001"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify INVENTORY_REJECTED notification",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Contains INVENTORY_REJECTED notification', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    const rejected = body.find(n => n.type === 'INVENTORY_REJECTED');",
            "    pm.expect(rejected).to.not.be.undefined;",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{notificationBaseUrl}}/api/notifications"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Cross-service COMMAND with sync response (dispatchAndReceive)",
      "description": "Demonstrates dispatchAndReceive() via RabbitMQ RPC.\nOrder Service sends ReserveInventoryCommand to Inventory Service and waits for the synchronous RESERVED/REJECTED response.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Reserve MONITOR-001 via Order Service (sync cross-service command)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Returns RESERVED from Inventory Service', () => {",
            "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.eql('RESERVED');",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders/order-sync-test/reserve",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"productId\": \"MONITOR-001\",\n  \"quantity\": 1\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify MONITOR-001 stock decreased",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Stock decreased to 4', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body.availableStock).to.eql(4);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventoryBaseUrl}}/api/inventory/products/MONITOR-001"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "7. Cross-service COMMAND with dispatchAndWait (no return value)",
      "description": "Demonstrates dispatchAndWait() via RabbitMQ RPC.\nOrder Service sends ReserveInventoryCommand to Inventory Service and waits for handler completion, but discards the return value.\nUseful when the caller needs to know if the command succeeded (to handle exceptions) but doesn't need the result.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Reserve MONITOR-001 via Order Service (dispatchAndWait)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Empty response body (dispatchAndWait returns no content)', () => {",
            "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.be.empty;",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders/order-wait-test/reserve-and-wait",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"productId\": \"MONITOR-001\",\n  \"quantity\": 1\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify MONITOR-001 stock decreased",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Stock decreased to 3', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body.availableStock).to.eql(3);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventoryBaseUrl}}/api/inventory/products/MONITOR-001"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "8. Validation middleware",
      "description": "PlaceOrderCommand uses @NotBlank, @Min, @Email annotations.\nCommandValidationInterceptor (built-in middleware) validates before the handler runs.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Place order with invalid data (400)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 400 - validation error', () => {",
            "    pm.response.to.have.status(400);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"productId\": \"\",\n  \"quantity\": 0,\n  \"customerEmail\": \"invalid\"\n}" }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "9. Add product (local command in Inventory Service)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Add MOUSE-001 product",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
            "pm.test('Returns product ID', () => {",
            "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.eql('MOUSE-001');",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{inventoryBaseUrl}}/api/inventory/products",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"productId\": \"MOUSE-001\",\n  \"name\": \"Wireless Mouse\",\n  \"initialStock\": 25\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify MOUSE-001 stock",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Stock is 25', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body.productId).to.eql('MOUSE-001');",
            "    pm.expect(body.availableStock).to.eql(25);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventoryBaseUrl}}/api/inventory/products/MOUSE-001"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "10. List all orders",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get all orders",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Returns array with orders', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body).to.be.an('array').and.have.length.at.least(2);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "11. Typed queries (ParameterizedTypeReference)",
      "description": "Demonstrates typed bus methods using ParameterizedTypeReference.\nThese endpoints use the overloaded ask() and dispatchAndReceive() methods that accept a ParameterizedTypeReference<R> parameter, ensuring correct generic type deserialization over RabbitMQ.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get all orders (typed local query)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Returns array with orders (typed)', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body).to.be.an('array').and.have.length.at.least(2);",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders/typed"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Check stock via Order Service (typed cross-service query)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Returns stock from Inventory Service via typed RabbitMQ query', () => {",
            "    const body = pm.response.json();",
            "    pm.expect(body.productId).to.eql('LAPTOP-001');",
            "    pm.expect(body.productName).to.eql('Gaming Laptop');",
            "    pm.expect(body.availableStock).to.be.a('number');",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders/stock/LAPTOP-001/typed"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Reserve MONITOR-001 (typed cross-service command)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Returns RESERVED from Inventory Service (typed)', () => {",
            "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.eql('RESERVED');",
            "});"
          ]}}],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{orderBaseUrl}}/api/orders/order-typed-test/reserve/typed",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"productId\": \"MONITOR-001\",\n  \"quantity\": 1\n}" }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
